# Repository Guidelines

## Project Structure & Module Organization
- `apps/api/` ‚Äì FastAPI services, routes, config, and database layer (`apps/api/services`, `apps/api/routes`).
- `apps/web/` ‚Äì Next.js front-end (`pages/`, `lib/`, `styles/`) with shared components under `components/`.
- `apps/worker/` ‚Äì Prefect flows, ingestion jobs, and maintenance tasks (e.g., `poc_pipeline.py`, `maintenance/retention.py`).
- `shared/` ‚Äì Cross-cutting libraries (connectors, data-context, feature store, storage helpers, schemas).
- `tests/` ‚Äì Pytest suites mirroring module layout; integration tests live alongside unit tests.
- `docs/` ‚Äì Living product docs (`ROADMAP.md`, `DEVELOPMENT.md`, etc.).

## Build, Test, and Development Commands
- `make api` / `make web` / `make worker` ‚Äì Run API, front-end, and worker dev servers with hot reload.
- `make lint` ‚Äì Execute Ruff + ESLint checks.
- `make test` ‚Äì Run Python pytest suites (API, worker, shared libs).
- `make smoke-context` ‚Äì End-to-end synthetic run exercising data-context tagging.
- `python apps/worker/run.py tenant-id` ‚Äì Launch Plan & Proof pipeline; append `--retention-only` or `--retention-after` for retention sweeps.

## Coding Style & Naming Conventions
- Python: PEP 8 with Ruff/Black defaults; prefer snake_case for functions/variables, PascalCase for classes.
- TypeScript/React: JSX with ESLint/Prettier settings; camelCase for functions/props, PascalCase for components.
- YAML/JSON: two-space indent, kebab-case keys for deployment manifests (e.g., `deployments/retention.yaml`).

## Testing Guidelines
- Pytest drives back-end and worker tests; Next.js relies on Jest/Playwright when added.
- Name tests `test_<module>.py` and mirror source hierarchy.
- Run targeted suites via `PYTHONPATH=.deps:. pytest tests/<path>`; prefer marking integration tests with `@pytest.mark.asyncio` where needed.
- Maintain coverage for critical flows: ingestion, modeling, allocator, API serialization.

## Commit & Pull Request Guidelines
- Write commits in present tense with concise scope tags (e.g., `worker: add retention webhook`); group related changes.
- Ensure commits lint and test clean locally before pushing.
- PRs should include: summary of changes, test evidence (`make test` output or screenshots for UI), linked Jira/GitHub issues, and rollout notes if config/secrets change.
- Request review from owners of touched modules (`apps/api`, `apps/web`, `shared/`); tag security/data stewards when modifying retention or connector logic.

## Security & Configuration Tips
- Secrets (Shopify tokens, OAuth creds) live in environment variables; never commit `.env` files.
- Use `JsonStateStore` for connector cursors and verify geocoding coverage metrics before enabling Autopilot for a tenant.

  "content": "\"\"\"Geocoding helpers for WeatherVane.\n\nUses `pgeocode` for offline postal lookups with an optional API fallback. Results are\ncached so repeated requests are fast. Geohashes are encoded at precision 5 (~4.9km).\n\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport os\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom functools import lru_cache\nfrom typing import Optional\n\nimport geohash2  # type: ignore\n\nif os.getenv(\"WEATHERVANE_DISABLE_PGEOCODE\") == \"1\":  # pragma: no cover - env override for incompatible builds\n    pgeocode = None  # type: ignore\nelse:  # pragma: no cover - optional dependency in production environments\n    try:\n        import pgeocode\n    except ImportError:\n        pgeocode = None  # type: ignore\n\nDEFAULT_COUNTRY = \"US\"\nDEFAULT_PRECISION = 5\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass GeoResult:\n    latitude: Optional[float]\n    longitude: Optional[float]\n    geohash: Optional[str]\n\n\nclass Geocoder:\n    def __init__(self, country: str = DEFAULT_COUNTRY, precision: int = DEFAULT_PRECISION) -> None:\n        self.country = country\n        self.precision = precision\n        self._nominatim = pgeocode.Nominatim(country) if pgeocode else None\n\n    @lru_cache(maxsize=10_000)\n    def lookup(self, postal_code: str, country: Optional[str] = None) -> GeoResult:\n        country = country or self.country\n        if not pgeocode:\n            return GeoResult(latitude=None, longitude=None, geohash=None)\n        nominatim = self._nominatim if country == self.country and self._nominatim else pgeocode.Nominatim(country)\n        record = nominatim.query_postal_code(str(postal_code))\n        lat = record.latitude\n        lon = record.longitude\n        if lat != lat or lon != lon:  # NaN check\n            return GeoResult(latitude=None, longitude=None, geohash=None)\n        geoh = geohash2.encode(float(lat), float(lon), self.precision)\n        return GeoResult(latitude=float(lat), longitude=float(lon), geohash=geoh)\n\n\ndef enrich_order_with_geo(order: dict, geocoder: Geocoder) -> dict:\n    shipping = order.get(\"shipping_address\") or {}\n    postal = shipping.get(\"zip\") or shipping.get(\"postal_code\") or order.get(\"shipping_postcode\")\n    country = shipping.get(\"country_code\") or shipping.get(\"country\") or DEFAULT_COUNTRY\n    if not postal:\n        return order\n    geo = geocoder.lookup(str(postal), country)\n    order[\"ship_latitude\"] = geo.latitude\n    order[\"ship_longitude\"] = geo.longitude\n    order[\"ship_geohash\"] = geo.geohash\n    return order\n"
}

if latest is None:\n        result = GeocodingCoverageResult(\n            tenant_id=tenant_id,\n            row_count=0,\n            geocoded_count=0,\n            ratio=0.0,\n            status=\"missing\",\n            details={\"message\": \"No orders dataset found\"},\n        )\n        _persist(summary_root, result)\n        return result\n\n    frame = read_parquet(latest)\n    if \"ship_geohash\" not in frame.columns:\n        result = GeocodingCoverageResult(\n            tenant_id=tenant_id,\n            row_count=frame.height,\n            geocoded_count=0,\n            ratio=0.0,\n            status=\"error\",\n            details={\"message\": \"ship_geohash column missing\", \"path\": str(latest)},\n        )\n        _persist(summary_root, result)\n        return
